\section{Components of a Computer}

\frame{
A computer is used to process data and a data processing system consists of more than just machines. A computer system must contain:
\begin{itemize}
\item hardware,
\item software,
\begin{itemize}
\item System software, and
\item Application software
\end{itemize}

\item humanware
\begin{itemize}
\item A system analyst
\item A programmer
\item A computer operator
\end{itemize}

\item operational procedures.
\end{itemize}

}

\section{Characteristics of the Computers}

\frame{
\begin{itemize}
\item Speed: It is related to the volume of data processed per unit of time. Computer can work very fast.
\item Accuracy: The degree of accuracy of computer is very high and every calculation is performed with the same accuracy.
\item Diligence: A computer is free from tiredness, lack of concentration, fatigue, etc. It can work for hours without creating any error.
\item Versatility: It means the capacity to perform completely different type of work.
\item Power of Remembering: Computer has the power of storing any amount of information or data.
\item No IQ: Computer is a dumb machine and it cannot do any work without instruction from the user.
\item No Feeling: It does not have feelings or emotion, taste, knowledge and experience.
\item Storage: The Computer has an in-built memory where it can store a large amount of data.
\end{itemize}

}

